This is one of my favourite photos of Hamilton. I forget exactly where it was taken but I believe it was near Wentworth and Burlington Streets. It was taken on 19 July 2008. \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl233\sa230
\cf0 It shows two dogs who are getting some fresh air and exercise on the roof of a front porch to a modest town-house, in a poor neighbourhood of Hamilton. \
They apparently got onto the roof through a small sliding window directly above the porch roof. \
This photo raises some interesting questions: \
<em>Did the dogs go out the window on their own or were they encouraged to so by someone?</em> \
\pard\pardeftab720\ri0\sl231\sa230
\cf0 <em>One possible scenario: the dogs were sent out there because they needed 'to get out' and the window was the most convenient exit. Is this what happened?</em> \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl233\sa230
\cf0 <em>Are the dogs in any danger of falling?</em> \
<em>Do the dogs enjoy being on the roof?</em> \
<em>Do the dogs urinate and defecate on the roof?</em> \
<em>What do the dogs think of someone taking their picture?</em> \
<em>Is having dogs on the roof a common occurrence or did I just happen by the only time it occurred?</em> \
<em>Are there people in the room behind and what are they doing?</em> \
\pard\pardeftab720\ri0\sl231
\cf0 <em>Is this a display of some kind of civic or personal dysfunction or is there something else going on? </em>]]></content:encoded> <excerpt:encoded><![CDATA[Two dogs get some fresh air and exercise on the roof of a front porch to a \
