\pard\pardeftab720\ri0\sl231\sa230
\cf0 The provincial <a href="http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/ottawa/story/2011/10/24/ontario-coroner-cycling-deathreview.html">coroner</a> will now examine the public health issues of cycling fatalities in the province. \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl233\sa230
\cf0 This is a good move because it takes the cycling debate away from excessive politicization (e.g. \'91war against the car\'92) into a less heated, more evidence-based, epidemiological direction. \
\pard\pardeftab720\ri0\sl233\sa230
\cf0 Most cyclists would agree that cycling in places like Toronto is much more dangerous than it needs to be. Lots of cyclists get killed. One reason is the limited scope of cycling infrastructure in the city. \
\pard\pardeftab720\ri0\sl233
\cf0 Toronto has an increasingly crowded and chronically underfunded public transit system. Cycling should be a sensible way of getting around town. But too often it isn't. Many more people would cycle in Toronto if only it were made safer.]]></content:encoded> \
